<section id="data-cleaning-and-validation" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="data-cleaning-and-validation">Data Cleaning and Validation<a class="anchorjs-link " aria-label="Anchor" data-anchorjs-icon="" href="https://melfitzsimmons-rstudio.tools.analytical-platform.service.justice.gov.uk/files/Time%20Series%20Practice/Electricity_demand_project.html#data-cleaning-and-validation" style="font: 1em / 1 anchorjs-icons; margin-left: 0.1875em; padding-right: 0.1875em; padding-left: 0.1875em;"></a></h2>
<p>The raw AEMO price and demand data were cleaned and transformed prior to analysis. Records were sorted chronologically and filtered to retain only trading interval observations. Key variables were renamed to improve readability, and timestamps were converted to a datetime format suitable for time series analysis.</p>
<p>Duplicate timestamps were checked to ensure data integrity. The data were then aggregated from trading intervals to hourly observations by calculating the average demand and wholesale electricity price within each hour.</p>
<p>To verify completeness, an expected sequence of hourly timestamps was generated and compared against the observed timestamps to identify any missing periods. Finally, summary statistics and dataset dimensions were reviewed to validate the cleaned dataset.</p>
