<p>Average electricity demand follows a consistent daily pattern across all years. Demand is lowest during the early morning hours (approximately 02:00-04:00), before increasing sharply to a morning peak around 07:00-08:00. Demand then declines through the late morning and early afternoon before rising again to a larger evening peak between 18:00 and 19:00. The evening peak is substantially higher than the morning peak.</p>
<p>Demand in 2025 is generally higher throughout the day and exhibits the largest evening peak, whereas demand in 2023 and 2026 is comparatively lower.</p>
