<p>Electricity demand exhibits clear seasonal variation throughout the year. Median demand is highest during the winter months, particularly June and July, where demand frequently exceeds 5,500 MW. In contrast, demand is generally lower during spring and late summer, with October to December exhibiting the lowest median demand levels.</p>
