<p>Seasonal naive models using daily, weekly and yearly lags were compared using time series cross-validation. The weekly seasonal naive model achieved the best accuracy, outperforming both the daily and yearly alternatives. This finding suggests that electricity demand is more closely related to demand observed during the same hour of the previous week than the previous day or year. Consequently, the weekly seasonal naive model was selected as the benchmark for subsequent comparisons with ETS and ARIMA models.</p>
