<p>We compare forecast accuracy and find that the the week model performed best overall, achieving the lowest RMSE (599.4) and MAPE (9.57%), indicating the most accurate forecasts overall. The ETS model produced slightly poorer results across all metrics, while ARIMA had the lowest MAE (409.7) but the highest errors in terms of RMSE and MAPE compared with the other top-performing models. The day model performed worst on all measures.</p>
